s qu’il donne sur la rédaction du </text:span><text:span text:style-name="T26">Monologium</text:span><text:span text:style-name="T24">, sur la manière dont il est né de discussions et de conversations que les frères le prièrent de rédiger comme </text:span><text:span text:style-name="T26">exemplum meditationis</text:span><text:span text:style-name="T24">.</text:span><text:span text:style-name="T27">302</text:span><text:span text:style-name="T24"> <text:tab/></text:span><text:span text:style-name="T25">VI</text:span><text:span text:style-name="T24">, t. CLVIII, p. 363.</text:span><text:span text:style-name="T27">303</text:span><text:span text:style-name="T24"> <text:tab/></text:span><text:span text:style-name="T25">VI</text:span><text:span text:style-name="T24">, t. CLVIII, p. 561, sq. ; ch. iv.</text:span><text:span text:style-name="T27">304</text:span><text:span text:style-name="T24"> <text:tab/></text:span><text:span text:style-name="T26">Monolog</text:span><text:span text:style-name="T24">., ch. xxxvi ; </text:span><text:span text:style-name="T25">VI</text:span><text:span text:style-name="T24">, t. CLVIII, p. 190-a.</text:span><text:span text:style-name="T27">305</text:span><text:span text:style-name="T24"> <text:tab/>Cur Deus Homo, ch. ii; </text:span><text:span text:style-name="T25">VI</text:span><text:span text:style-name="T24">, t. CLVIII, p. 362 : etiam si nulla ratione quod credo possim comprehendere, nihil tarnen est quod me ab ejus firmitate valeat evellere.</text:span><text:span text:style-name="T27">306</text:span><text:span text:style-name="T24"> <text:tab/></text:span><text:span text:style-name="T26">De Fide Trinitatis</text:span><text:span text:style-name="T24">, </text:span><text:span text:style-name="T25">VI</text:span><text:span text:style-name="T24">, t. CLVIII, p. 259.</text:span><text:span text:style-name="T27">307</text:span><text:span text:style-name="T24"> <text:tab/></text:span><text:span text:style-name="T26">Cur Deus Homo</text:span><text